created: undefined, last updated: 2026-04-03, [Read more](https://mastra.ai/docs/workflows/suspend-and-resume)

## Pausing a workflow with suspend() Direct link to pausing-a-workflow-with-suspend
Use `suspend()` to pause workflow execution at a specific step.
You can define a suspend condition in the step’s `execute` block using values from `resumeData`.
- If the condition isn’t met, the workflow pauses and returns `suspend()`.
- If the condition is met, the workflow continues with the remaining logic in the step.
